Hi! I am a researcher interested in developing data driven insights to inform public policy. I currently work as a Research Associate at the Department of Economics and Public Policy, Indian School of Business Hyderabad with Ashwini Chhatre and Avik Sarkar.
My interdisciplinary pursuits span across fields Urban and Regional Planning, Real Estate, Economics and Public Policy. I am currently working on;
Infrastructure Policy: Studying the equity implications of capital investments in large-scale infrastructure on demography, land acquisition and the environment; Food Systems: Designing experiments and policies for promoting cultivation, public distribution and consumption of sustainable millets in regions vulnerable to climate change, and lastly, Digital Identity: understanding the potential of unique digital identity in India to inform bureaucratic decision making for food, employment and scholarship welfare schemes.
